title: Pool Hopping
description: Garnet and Steven explore the most unlikely timelines in Beach City.

title: Drawn to Making It Happen with Sidney Keys
description: Cartoon Network and Sidney Keys III are making it happen! Sidney Tells Craig of the Creek and his sister Jessica about Black representation in literature and his cool book club, Books N Bros!

title: Craig and the Kid's Table
description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

title: Jail Break
description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

title: #FightAtTheMuseum
description: Supergirl always relies on her strength, but she'll need more than brawn to stop brainy Catwoman from stealing valuable gems from the local science museum.

title: Escape from Family Dinner
description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

title: #Abracadabrapalooza
description: In an attempt to make Karen feel better about a pimple, Zee recounts her embarrassing transition into magichood, and the rift it created between her and her father.

title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 2
description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

title: Smile Bones
description: When Cyborg and Beast Boy teach the other Titans to wolf down their food, the gang develops a big fat problem.

title: Little Buddies
description: Cyborg wants Pain Bot to be his "little buddy" but is the destructive robot too dangerous to be a sidekick?

title: BBCYFSHIPBDAY
description: Beast Boy and Cyborg celebrate the birthday of their friendship.

title: Craig of the Beach
description: Craig gets to hit the beach with his friends and family, but starts to get worried his Dad is more fun than him.

title: Hero of the Month: Bumblebee
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Bumblebee. Waller shows a video montage of Bumblebee's exploits including saving her friends plus little comedic beats where Bumblebee changing size causes her to split a seam in her costume.

title: The Cape
description: The Titans reminisce about the time they threw a surprise party for Cinderblock.

title: #MeetTheCheetah
description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

title: Drawn To Thinking Big
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Black History Month!  Join Philip Solomon, voice of "Craig" on Craig of the Creek, as he interviews 12-year-old Elijah Precciely, child prodigy and college sophomore. Discover why Elijah is Drawn To Thinking Big!

title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

title: Lucky Stars
description: Raven explains astrology to the Titans and tells their horoscopes, but Cyborg does not believe.

title: The Ground Is Lava!
description: When an intense game of "The Ground is Lava" breaks out, Craig must carefully traverse the Creek to save his sister.

title: Oil Drums
description: Cyborg wants to have an '80s TV show marathon, but the remote is missing.

title: #SuperWho?
description: Overwhelmed by the amount of Superman coverage in Metropolis, Supergirl decides to get out there and really show the city what she can do. But when Superman inadvertently puts everyone in harm's way, Supergirl has to decide whether to do what's good for the people or what's good for her ego.

title: Future Vision
description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

title: The Return of Slade
description: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.

title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

title: Superhero Feud
description: Control Freak pits the Titans against the DC Superhero Girls to determine who is the best team in the universe.

title: Fort Williams
description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

title: Lazy Sunday
description: When the Titans replace the couch with a treadmill, Cyborg and Beast Boy must get guidance from the couch spirit.

title: #SweetJustice Part 2
description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

title: Grandma Voice
description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

title: Camper on the Run
description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

title: Legs from Here to Homeworld
description: Steven travels to visit family.

title: Double Trouble
description: Cyborg and Beast Boy create clones of themselves to do their chores and the clones create more clones until the situation grows out of control.

title: Burger vs. Burrito
description: Cyborg and Beast Boy face off about which is better, burgers or burritos.

title: Monster in the Garden
description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

title: Keeping It Together
description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

title: Jessica's Trail
description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

title: Drawn To Happiness
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Black History Month!  Join Philip Solomon, voice of "Craig" on Craig of the Creek, as he interviews 15-year-old Grace Callwood, founder of the We Cancerve Movement, Inc.  Discover how Grace is Drawn To Happiness!

title: Real Boy Adventures
description: When he transforms into "Fleshy Guy," Cyborg discovers the joy and pain of being human.

title: Drawn To Helping Others
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Black History Month!  Join Philip Solomon, voice of "Craig" on Craig of the Creek, as he interviews 12-year-old Jahkil Jackson, founder of Project I Am. Discover how Jahkil is Drawn To Helping Others!

title: Cousin of the Creek
description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

title: #Frenemies Part 2
description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

title: In the Key of the Creek
description: When a rainy day keeps Craig inside, he uses his toys and imagination to create his own Creek adventure in Craig of the Creek's first musical episode!

title: Brobots
description: Cyborg comes to visit Beast Boy, but once Cyborg realizes how much he and Robotman have in common, they become inseparable.

title: The Answer
description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

title: #Frenemies Part 1
description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

title: Had to Be There
description: So she isn't left out of inside jokes, the Titans time travel to past adventures and insert Bumblebee into their memories.

title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 1
description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

title: Keystone Motel
description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

title: #Beeline
description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

title: Drawn To Music
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Black History Month!  Join Philip Solomon, voice of "Craig" on Craig of the Creek, as he interviews 5-year-old Justin "L.J." Wilson, drummer and musical marvel!  Discover how L.J. is Drawn To Music!

title: #TweenTitans
description: Jessica Cruz is hired by billionaire playboy Bruce Wayne to chaperone young Dick Grayson's Metropolis birthday bash and brings Karen Beecher along to help, but the girls get more than they bargained for when the TWEEN party guests reveal their TITANic personalities.

title: #TheBirdAndTheBee
description: Meek little Karen Beecher is intimidated by big broody Carter Hall - both as a hero and a teen - until she discovers Hawkman's tragically romantic destiny and vows to use her vast knowledge of cheesy teen movies to help him reunite with his beloved.

title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 1
description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

title: #SweetJustice Part 1
description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

title: Sadie Killer
description: Steven and the Cool Kids start a band, but they have trouble finding their sound.

title: The Evolution of Craig
description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

title: Bumblebee
description: Get to know the new Super Hero Girl - Bumblebeel/Karen Beecher - starring in the new DC Super Hero Girls series on Cartoon Network!

title: Various Modes of Transportation
description: With the other Titans away, Cyborg is forced to take a road trip with Robin.

title: Cheeseburger Backpack
description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

title: Trick or Creek
description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

title: #SheMightBeGiant
description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

title: Forest Pirates
description: The Titans are at Super Hero Summer Camp for the week and they may need to add another teammate to win the big canoe race.

title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 2
description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

title: #PlightOfTheBumblebee
description: Karen Beecher needs to get to class to preserve her perfect attendance but can't get out of her malfunctioning Bumblebee suit.
